1
00:00:14,439 --> 00:00:15,960
Hello, darling.

2
00:00:16,239 --> 00:00:17,559
Come save me, quick.

3
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:18,760
Someone's trying to kill me.

4
00:00:19,039 --> 00:00:19,960
Calm down.

5
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:21,359
What happened?

6
00:00:21,879 --> 00:00:23,800
Someone... someone broke into my house.

7
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:25,120
He's threatening me with a knife.

8
00:00:25,359 --> 00:00:26,519
He's making me hand over

9
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:28,480
all our external accounts from recent years

10
00:00:29,199 --> 00:00:30,679
and... and all the files.

11
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,359
That night,

12
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:21,000
your wife was startled awake the same way?

13
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:47,239
For slandering and framing me like this,

14
00:01:49,519 --> 00:01:51,560
I reserve the right to sue you.

15
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:52,760
You want evidence?

16
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:54,599
Fine.

17
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,280
Recognize this person?

18
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,799
Although you wore a mask,

19
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:08,960
after technical analysis,

20
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:11,199
this man buying beer

21
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,439
matches your features perfectly.

22
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,439
President Su.

23
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:23,280
Not enough, is it?

24
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:32,840
The man cleaning at Shen Qing's home

25
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,039
is Fengdu Bank President, Su Zhuang.

26
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,520
See it clearly?

27
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:39,800
Absolutely certain.

28
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:42,000
I often work near the bank.

29
00:02:42,439 --> 00:02:43,360
I recognize him.

30
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:47,360
You mean Su Zhuang took a rag and vacuum,

31
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:50,199
and cleaned every corner of Shen Qing's room?

32
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:52,280
Probably the entire house.

33
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,280
While he was cleaning,

34
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,280
I managed to sneak out.

35
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,400
I was so scared at the time,

36
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,360
I just wanted to get out of there.

37
00:02:59,879 --> 00:03:01,400
I only took Shen Qing's necklace,

38
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,560
I didn't touch anything else.

39
00:03:10,759 --> 00:03:12,599
Still doubting his story?

40
00:03:17,199 --> 00:03:18,960
Speak! Why did you kill Shen Qing?

41
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:21,439
I didn't. I didn't kill her.

42
00:03:24,919 --> 00:03:26,479
I want to confront him face to face.

43
00:03:27,479 --> 00:03:28,639
He's just spouting Empty words.

44
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,080
It doesn't mean it was me!

45
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:32,199
I knew you'd still deny it.

46
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:36,080
Keep listening.

47
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,840
It gets better.

48
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,719
How can you prove what you said?

49
00:03:41,479 --> 00:03:43,039
Through a gap in the curtains,

50
00:03:43,759 --> 00:03:45,719
I secretly took a few photos.

51
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,120
They're just a bit blurry.

52
00:03:48,759 --> 00:03:49,800
We sent the photos

53
00:03:50,479 --> 00:03:51,439
to the tech department,

54
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:53,680
and had them enhance the clarity.

55
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,800
Open your eyes wide

56
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,560
and take a good look.

57
00:04:09,719 --> 00:04:10,360
President Su,

58
00:04:11,639 --> 00:04:12,479
the text next to you,

59
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:13,879
you should recognize it, right?

60
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:31,040
Hello, darling.

61
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,480
Come save me, quickly.

62
00:04:32,759 --> 00:04:33,920
Someone's trying to kill me.

63
00:04:34,160 --> 00:04:35,040
Don't panic.

64
00:04:35,399 --> 00:04:36,480
What happened?

65
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,839
Someone broke into my house.

66
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:40,199
He threatened me with a knife.

67
00:04:40,439 --> 00:04:43,680
He demanded our external accounts

68
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:46,000
and... and the files from recent years.

69
00:04:46,279 --> 00:04:47,120
Did you give them to him?

70
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:48,120
I...

71
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:51,000
No way! What are you saying?

72
00:04:51,759 --> 00:04:53,600
I balanced those books long ago.

73
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:57,000
How could I back up such damning evidence?

74
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,439
Don't panic.

75
00:05:00,959 --> 00:05:02,680
Chengming Machinery's under investigation.

76
00:05:02,839 --> 00:05:04,079
Someone's getting nervous.

77
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:05,439
Where are you?

78
00:05:05,879 --> 00:05:07,800
I... I escaped.

79
00:05:08,199 --> 00:05:09,639
I don't want to die.

80
00:05:09,959 --> 00:05:11,639
I have to see you right now.

81
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:13,399
Otherwise, I'll call the police.

82
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:14,839
Don't be rash, darling.

83
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,319
Here's what we'll do.

84
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,199
Let's meet at the bank.

85
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:19,519
Wait for me in the office.

86
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:22,360
Okay, hurry up.

87
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,079
Wait, darling.

88
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:27,959
The office has surveillance cameras.

89
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,800
Climb the fire escape from the back yard.

90
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,480
Go to the rooftop and wait for me there.

91
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,040
Okay, okay, okay.

92
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,720
I'm giving you one last chance.

93
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,079
How did Shen Qing really die?

94
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,959
Shen Qing,

95
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,959
the night she was attacked,

96
00:06:19,279 --> 00:06:21,399
after she escaped, she called me

97
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:22,920
and insisted on seeing me.

98
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,120
I was afraid she'd do something stupid,

99
00:06:26,639 --> 00:06:28,720
so after settling my wife down,

100
00:06:29,319 --> 00:06:31,120
I snuck out to meet her.

101
00:06:32,439 --> 00:06:34,079
Quite the "settling down."

102
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,319
You're pretty slick.

103
00:06:49,839 --> 00:06:52,920
I just added a little liquor to the wine.

104
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,399
President Su,

105
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,160
let me give you a piece of advice.

106
00:06:57,279 --> 00:06:59,399
You'd better just come clean.

107
00:07:00,279 --> 00:07:01,959
Don't harbor any illusions.

108
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:03,839
Understood?

109
00:07:09,439 --> 00:07:10,240
Shen Qing.

110
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,399
President Su, President Su!

111
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,639
You're finally here!

112
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,000
Someone's trying to kill me!

113
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,120
Don't panic.

114
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:19,560
Here.

115
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,600
Have a drink, calm down.

116
00:07:22,879 --> 00:07:23,839
What's actually going on?

117
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:26,240
I... I...

118
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,319
I was too greedy.

119
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,240
I knew Wu Chengming's firm couldn't repay,

120
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,279
but I still helped make False accounts

121
00:07:33,439 --> 00:07:34,639
to get the loan approved.

122
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,279
I really know I was wrong.

123
00:07:36,439 --> 00:07:37,879
Please, you have to save me.

124
00:07:38,439 --> 00:07:39,720
How dare you do that?

125
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,920
That's breaking the law, you know?

126
00:07:42,279 --> 00:07:43,240
I know.

127
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,879
I've known all along.

128
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,680
President Su, save me.

129
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:48,800
Give me one more chance.

130
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,040
Give me one more chance.

131
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,720
I'll absolutely never do this again.

132
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:53,120
I'm begging you.

133
00:07:57,839 --> 00:07:59,319
How much did Wu Chengming pay you?

134
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:04,240
Three... three million.

135
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,879
You've got some nerve.

136
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:09,439
I really know I was wrong.

137
00:08:10,399 --> 00:08:12,000
I'll return the money tomorrow.

138
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,600
I won't keep a single cent.

139
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:18,000
President Su, I know I was wrong.

140
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,600
Right now,

141
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,839
there's only one way to help you.

142
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,800
What way?

143
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,240
President Su, tell me, what way?

144
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:32,559
Tomorrow, I'll go with you to surrender.

145
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,159
No.

146
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,919
I... I can't go to the police.

147
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,600
I don't want to go to prison.

148
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,559
President Su, President Su.

149
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:44,960
President Su, I'm begging you.

150
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,440
You must have some other way.

151
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,720
This is the only way to save you.

152
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:52,879
As long as you confess voluntarily

153
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,360
and turn in all the money you took,

154
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:57,480
the court will give you a lenient sentence.

155
00:08:57,639 --> 00:08:59,679
A few years in prison and you'll be out.

156
00:08:59,679 --> 00:09:01,039
Better than losing your life.

157
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,639
Tomorrow,

158
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,279
I'll be waiting for you at the office.

159
00:09:09,279 --> 00:09:10,080
President Su.

160
00:09:10,679 --> 00:09:11,559
President Su.

161
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:18,919
Director Shen?

162
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:29,519
Shen...

163
00:10:52,759 --> 00:10:53,840
After all this beating around the bush,

164
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,000
you just want to say Shen Qing jumped.

165
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:59,080
But it was clearly suicide to escape justice.

166
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,559
Why did you two meet on the rooftop?

167
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,000
I asked her to come to the office.

168
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,000
She said the office had cameras.

169
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,399
She insisted on the rooftop.

170
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:09,279
But I never imagined she'd kill herself.

171
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,200
Fine.

172
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,919
Playing "The dead can't testify", huh?

173
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,159
If you don't believe me,

174
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:19,519
go ahead and investigate.

175
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,080
If there's no evidence,

176
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,919
let me out of here now.

177
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:26,799
I've got a pile of bank business waiting.

178
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:29,679
Then why clean Shen Qing's place later?

179
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,720
What were you trying to cover up?

180
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:44,240
About half a month ago,

181
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:46,279
it was Shen Qing's birthday.

182
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,000
She insisted I come to her place.

183
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:50,960
Said she'd invited some friends too.

184
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:53,639
I couldn't refuse, so I went.

185
00:11:54,279 --> 00:11:54,799
But...

186
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:58,240
she's already dead.

187
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,320
I don't want to talk about this.

188
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,399
What was your relationship?

189
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,440
Just colleagues.

190
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,639
Colleagues?

191
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,720
Then what's there to hide?

192
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,639
I've said everything I need to.

193
00:12:07,039 --> 00:12:09,559
No, you keep Dodging the key issues.

194
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:11,000
You haven't said a word about what matters.

195
00:12:13,559 --> 00:12:14,679
Just ordinary colleagues?

196
00:12:14,679 --> 00:12:15,919
Then why do you have her house key?

197
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:17,519
She gave it to me.

198
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:18,919
Why didn't she give one to me?

199
00:12:37,159 --> 00:12:37,840
Fine.

200
00:12:39,159 --> 00:12:39,840
I'll talk.

201
00:12:52,639 --> 00:12:54,000
President Su, come in.

202
00:13:02,519 --> 00:13:03,360
Where's everyone else?

203
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,399
Tonight it's just you and me.

204
00:13:11,679 --> 00:13:12,360
Shen Qing,

205
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,159
this isn't appropriate.

206
00:13:14,799 --> 00:13:16,320
I have things to do. I'm leaving.

207
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,600
How I truly feel...

208
00:13:21,039 --> 00:13:23,080
Do you not get it, or are you pretending?

209
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,799
I'm a married man.

210
00:13:28,519 --> 00:13:31,080
Your marriage has been in name only.

211
00:13:34,759 --> 00:13:35,679
You can leave if you want,

212
00:13:36,639 --> 00:13:38,840
but tell me to my face you don't love me.

213
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:41,080
Then I'll never bother you again.

214
00:14:12,399 --> 00:14:13,399
That night

215
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,519
was the first time you two were together

216
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,159
The first time

217
00:14:18,399 --> 00:14:19,840
and also the only time

218
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:22,240
Afterwards, she gave me her house key.

219
00:14:24,879 --> 00:14:27,039
The night she went to kill herself,

220
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,000
I was afraid of leaving traces there,

221
00:14:30,679 --> 00:14:32,159
so I went to clean up

222
00:14:32,559 --> 00:14:34,120
"Purely colleagues?"

223
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,159
That's pretty pure indeed.

224
00:14:40,559 --> 00:14:42,320
I'm a normal man too

225
00:14:42,679 --> 00:14:43,960
In that situation,

226
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,480
I couldn't resist.

227
00:14:49,519 --> 00:14:50,919
A Bank President, no less.

228
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,480
Even your way of making excuses

229
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,639
is so distinctively unique.

230
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,960
But if you just wanted a one-night stand,

231
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,320
why did you take her key?

232
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:02,200
I didn't want to,

233
00:15:02,639 --> 00:15:03,919
but she insisted.

234
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:06,759
If I had flat-out refused,

235
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,080
it would have hurt her feelings.

236
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,279
You understand?

237
00:15:10,679 --> 00:15:12,600
You really are quite sanctimonious.

238
00:15:13,559 --> 00:15:14,519
Hey, I want to ask you,

239
00:15:15,159 --> 00:15:17,759
do you think you're some kind of gentleman?

240
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,080
Shen Qing being with you,

241
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:23,080
was really her terrible luck.

242
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:26,840
What do you mean?

243
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:29,279
Investigate the case if you must,

244
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,000
but why the personal attacks?

245
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:32,919
Captain Li,

246
00:15:34,639 --> 00:15:37,159
my behavior is, at most, cheating.

247
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,960
That doesn't break the law, does it?

248
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,320
Cheating indeed isn't a criminal offense,

249
00:15:44,519 --> 00:15:46,200
but murder is a different story.

250
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:48,879
Captain Li,

251
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,639
you can eat whatever you want,

252
00:15:53,879 --> 00:15:55,559
but you can't say whatever you want.

253
00:15:57,399 --> 00:15:59,360
Am I connected to Shen Qing's death?

254
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:01,159
Have I ever killed anyone?

255
00:16:01,519 --> 00:16:02,120
Huh?

256
00:16:02,919 --> 00:16:04,559
As police officers,

257
00:16:04,799 --> 00:16:07,600
can you just casually frame a good man?

258
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:09,879
Are you fit to call yourself a good man?

259
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,919
Take a look at yourself.

260
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,320
Wearing a suit and tie,

261
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:15,679
holding the title of Bank President,

262
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:17,679
doing nothing but filthy, sordid things.

263
00:16:19,279 --> 00:16:20,639
You're pushing all the blame

264
00:16:20,639 --> 00:16:22,000
onto a dead person.

265
00:16:23,279 --> 00:16:24,320
Do you still have a conscience?

266
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,960
Or were you born without one?

267
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,679
Then Captain Li, let me ask you,

268
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,279
you say I'm guilty,

269
00:16:39,159 --> 00:16:40,720
so show me the evidence

270
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,480
Accusing me of murder without evidence,

271
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:47,879
I'll sue you

272
00:16:48,039 --> 00:16:49,440
A loan of fifty-five million,

273
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:51,120
could Shen Qing decide on that alone?

274
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,840
Without your authorization,

275
00:16:53,159 --> 00:16:54,919
who could approve such a massive loan?

276
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,080
You killed Shen Qing with your own hands.

277
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:02,840
You're the Executioner who doomed her.

278
00:17:03,159 --> 00:17:03,919
Understand?

279
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:18,480
I admit I was at fault here.

280
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,279
If only back then

281
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,839
I had supervised this loan more strictly,

282
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:28,000
she wouldn't have fallen into the abyss

283
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,240
But I had no malicious intent.

284
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:34,799
I never thought she'd kill herself.

